<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-24T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.00/126</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-24T20:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 25, 7.30
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>366. <persName corresp="#p_VEK1">Venizelos</persName> and some
                                members of his cabinet now in Piraeus Harbor. <hi rend="italic">Pourparlers</hi> going on between them and <persName corresp="#p_ZA1">Zaimis</persName> Government concerning terms
                                of reconciliation for union of Greece. Reported that <persName corresp="#p_ZA1">Zaimis</persName> will resign as he finds
                                certain terms unacceptable, particularly that the Venizelist Chamber
                                of Deputies of June, 1915, should be convoked. <persName corresp="#p_VEK1">Venizelos</persName> maintains that present
                                Chamber of Deputies elected January, 1916, is illegal.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>